[Several similar press reports were received from Mary Marshall,
reiterating that the single suspected case in Gujarat has not been
confirmed and, in fact, that the patient had no contact with poultry.
A total of 95 clinical samples from people who have had contact with
poultry are now under test at the National Institute of Virology in
Pune and the National Institute of Communicable Diseases in Delhi.
None appear to have been referred to a WHO reference laboratory. -
Mod.CP]
